This endpoint allows the user to update the tags associated with a specific task by sending an HTTP PUT request to the specified URL.

### Request Body

- The request should include a JSON payload with the following parameter:

    - `name`: (string) The name of the tag to be updated.


### Response

The response to this request will be in JSON format with the following properties:

- `message`: (string) A message indicating the result of the request.

- `data`: (null) The data associated with the request, which is null in this case.

- `success`: (boolean) Indicates whether the request was successful.


### Example Response

``` json
{
    "message": "",
    "data": null,
    "success": true
}

 ```

### JSON Schema for Response

``` json
{
    "type": "object",
    "properties": {
        "message": {
            "type": "string"
        },
        "data": {
            "type": "null"
        },
        "success": {
            "type": "boolean"
        }
    },
    "required": ["message", "data", "success"]
}

 ```

